      "alt": "A dark-themed screenshot of a Polymarket prediction page titled \"When will GPT-5.6 be released?\". The top half features a complex, volatile line graph tracking four potential outcome windows from mid-May to June 11, 2026. The bottom half lists the specific bet choices, their current percentage probabilities, and trading buttons.\n\n**Visual Observations & Layout Nuances:**\n\n* **Graph Structure:** The chart plots percentage odds (0% to 80%) on the vertical axis against a timeline on the horizontal axis. Four colored lines overlap and crisscross intensely, illustrating highly erratic market sentiment and sharp, sudden spikes over the weeks.\n* **The Dominant Trend:** The light blue line representing the \"June 22–June 28\" window sits at the top right of the graph, showing a dramatic upward surge in early June to become the leading prediction.\n* **The Fading Trend:** Conversely, the orange line (\"June 8–June 14\") had a massive peak around late May, accounting for nearly 70% probability, but has since crashed dramatically toward the bottom of the chart.\n* **Data Discrepancy:** There is a slight visual discrepancy between the legend at the top and the active market list below. The top legend rounds the leading prediction to 53.6%, while the active trading row below shows it updated to 54%.\n* **UI Elements:** Green \"Buy Yes\" and red \"Buy No\" betting buttons sit on the right side of each prediction row, designed to look like active, clickable stock-trading interfaces.",
